        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Navistar has identified the following changes to improve heating and cooling for the sleeper area
                    in 9200, 9300 and 9400 Pro Sleeper Model vehicles built before October 1, 1995. The improvement
                    includes adding insulation to the plenum and bunk area. TSM's have a video (TCN-95314) that explains
                    the service procedure for adding the insulation to the plenum area, along with additional diagnostic
                    information for the heater/AC system.
                </para>
                <para>A heavy duty blower motor has also been released for this model vehicle. It will be necessary to
                    inspect the heater A/C unit and plenum to determine if the blower motors have been replaced. Refer
                    to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="hl9591001">BLOWER MOTOR INSPECTION AND REPLACEMENT</hotlnk>
                    for information to identify the new motor and for the replacement procedure.
                </para>
                <para>This Authorized Field Change provides parts, service information and labor times to make these
                    changes.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
