        <svcproc id="hl9591002" svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="5">
            <title>SEAL SLEEPER AREA</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect passenger seat belt brackets.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove passenger seat.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove trim panels that cover the A/C heater unit under the passenger seat.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the flexible hose between the A/C heater unit and the plenum blower cover plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591001">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9591001" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9591001" filename="../afcfigures/g9591001.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the outlet duct on the bottom of the plenum blower cover plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591002">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9591002" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9591002" filename="../afcfigures/g9591002.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the screws that secure the plenum blower cover plate to the plenum and pull the
                    plate out enough to see the electrical connectors.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unplug the electrical connectors and remove the plenum blower cover plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Go to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="hl9591001">BLOWER MOTOR INSPECTION AND REPLACEMENT</hotlnk>
                    now. Inspect all blower motors. If any old style (Siemans) motors are found, replace them with the
                    new heavy duty (Fasco) motor. Do not replace any new (Fasco) motors that are found.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the foam insulation from the floor and walls of the plenum.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Seal the gap between the vertical plastic duct and the top sheet metal piece ("A,"
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591002">Figure 2</hotlnk>) with black sticky-back foam.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">All holes in the top sheet of the plenum and the side gusset must be sealed with duct
                    tape or tape sealer ("B,"
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591002">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The upper corner of the rear panel of plenum ("C,"
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591002">Figure 2</hotlnk>) must be sealed. Pack with green foam.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a wiring grommet P/N 2009578C1 in the lower portion of the rear panel ("D,"
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591002">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install sticky back foam P/N 1699224C1 (triangular shape) in the bottom of the plenum
                    chamber (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591002">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Roll excess upward, stick to outer wall.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install sticky back foam P/N 1699223C1 (rectangular shape) on the outside wall of the
                    plenum (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591002">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Install over rolled up edge of triangular piece
                    installed in Step 14.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On the inside of the sleeper, along the back wall, from side to side, place one piece of
                    plastic angle P/N 1699528C1 with the vertical part of the angle behind the back wall trim and the
                    horizontal part of the angle resting on the plywood bunk base (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591003">Figure 3</hotlnk>). Begin sliding angle in at seat belt cutout in back
                    panel. Install second piece at opposite seat belt cutout and overlap ends of plastic angle
                    approximately 3/4 inch and attach to bunk board with pan head screw P/N 24379R1.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9591003" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9591003" filename="../afcfigures/g9591003.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From inside the cargo compartment, or inside the sleeper, stuff the strips of green foam
                    P/N 2031754C2 into the area between the back trim panel and the bunk support angles (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591003">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From inside the sleeper, close the gap between the two pieces of plywood bunk base with
                    duct tape.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From inside the cargo compartment, on the forward wall of the compartment, in both
                    outside compartments (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591004">Figure 4</hotlnk>), cover all the openings in the forward wall with duct
                    tape (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591004">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9591004" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9591004" filename="../afcfigures/g9591004.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the plenum blower cover plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591005">Figure 5</hotlnk>) in position in front of the plenum opening and plug the
                    electrical connectors together. Be sure they are completely connected together to prevent them from
                    disconnecting at a later time.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9591005" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9591005" filename="../afcfigures/g9591005.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the plenum blower plate cover in position (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591005">Figure 5</hotlnk>) with the screws removed in Step 6.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the outlet duct to the bottom of the plenum blower plate cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591005">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install flexible hose.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the trim panels that cover the A/C heater unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the passenger seat and tighten mounting bolts to 20-22 ft-lbs. (27-30 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install seat belt. Tighten mounting bolt in sill to 70-85 ft-lbs. (95-115 Nm) and
                    shoulder bolt to 25-30 ft-lbs. (34-47 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc id="hl9591001" svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
            <title>BLOWER MOTOR INSPECTION AND REPLACEMENT</title>
            <para>To identify the new motor against the old motor, refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9591006">Figure 6</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9591007">Figure 7</hotlnk>. Any old style motor that is identified will require
                replacement with a new heavy duty motor P/N 1698779C1. If a new heavy duty motor is identified, it
                should not be replaced. The heavy duty motor will mount in the same opening as the old style motor.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9591006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g9591006" filename="../afcfigures/g9591006.webp" type="webp" resolution="100"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Old Style Motor</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f9591007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g9591007" filename="../afcfigures/g9591007.webp" type="webp" resolution="100"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. New Style Motor</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the scuff plate from the door sill.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the floor mat and cover from the Blend-Air housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the screws securing the Blend-Air housing cover plate. Remove cover plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Perform blower motor identification. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591006">Figure 6</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591007">Figure 7</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove blower motor as required. If replacement is not required, go to Step 16. If
                    required, continue with Step 6.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector and ground wire from the old blower motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591008">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9591008" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9591008" filename="../afcfigures/g9591008.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the vent tube from the blower motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591008">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the blower motor five (5) mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591008">Figure 8</hotlnk>) and remove the blower motor assembly from the vehicle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the blower wheel from the motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the blower wheel on the new motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Plug the electrical connector removed from the old blower motor into the pig tail on the
                    new blower motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591009">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9591009" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9591009" filename="../afcfigures/g9591009.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the blower motor assembly (with new motor) in the heater or heater-A/C unit.
                    Install and tighten the five (5) mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591009">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the ground lead removed from the old blower motor, along with the ground lead
                    pig tail extending from the new blower motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9591009">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the blower motor vent.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test for operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install Blend-Air housing cover plate with screws removed in Step 3.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reposition floor mat.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the scuff plate in the door sill.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Return to Step 9 of
                    <hotlnk xrefid="hl9591002">SEAL SLEEPER AREA</hotlnk>
                    and complete the air plenum sealing repair.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
