        <claims>
            <para>Please note the special procedures which must be followed for any blower motor replacement in the
                claim coding section under the 5 digit group identifier.
            </para>
            <para>Expense is to be charged to Warranty. Claims are to be submitted in the normal manner, making
                reference to
                <hotlnk xrefid="afcclaim">Authorized Field Change</hotlnk>
                Number G-95910, except for blower motor replacement. When blower motor replacement is necessary, a
                special section must be added to the claim and reference G-95614.
            </para>
            <figure id="afcclaim" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="afclaim" filename="../afcfigures/afclaim.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
            </figure>
            <para>It is important that the coding be completed properly to assist in processing the warranty claim.
                Complete instructions will be found in the Warranty Manual, Section 7-1. Special attention should be
                given to items 39 through 44.
            </para>
            <para>To assure this important improvement is made in a timely manner, all claims for G-95910 activity must
                be submitted by January 31, 1997, or within the normal warranty period for the vehicle, if after January
                31, 1997.
            </para>
